com.quest.glue.api.services
Interface CommonTopologyInfo

public interface CommonTopologyInfo

The class (available through the SystemInfoService4 for local values or the SSHConnection2 and WindowsInfoConnection for remote values) provides values that can be used with the Host and OperatingSystem topology objects. The format of the values returned by this interface are only to be used for populating the host model and take into account historical requirements.

Each of the methods in this interface must indicate which topology object properties it is intended for.

Since:
5.6.7

Method Detail

getHostName

java.lang.String getHostName()
Returns the canonical host name for the system or null if a canonical name could not be determined. The name should be used for the " Host.name" topology property.

NOTE: If a host display name has been configured for FglAM (either manually or automatically) that host display name will be returned when requesting the host name for the current host (via the SystemInfoService4). The standard host name will be returned when obtaining information from a remote system, even if that remote system has a FglAM installed on it.

Care should be taken when writing agent that uses this method. Agent should allow end users to override the host name so that the agent can be configured to return the same value as the FglAM host display name.

Returns:
the canonical host name, or null

getHostPrimaryIPAddress

java.lang.String getHostPrimaryIPAddress()
Determines the primary IP address of the interface associated with the default route. This value should be used for the "Host.primaryIPAddress" topology property. Using this method will ensure that the same value is used no matter which agent collects the data and will prevent topology churn.

Returns:
The primary IP address of the interface associated with the default route or null if it is not available.
Since:
5.6.10

getHostSystemID

java.lang.String getHostSystemID()
The unique system ID for system, or null if the system ID could not be determined. The system ID should be used for the "Host.systemId" topology property.

the unique system ID, or null
